==English==

{{rank|about|its|time|74|only|like|little|now}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əʊnliː/}}
* {{audio|en-us-only.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[ænlic]]''
===Adjective===
'''only''' (''no comparative or superlative forms'')
# singular; part of a relatively small number
#: ''he is the '''only''' doctor for miles''
# without [[sibling]]; without a sibling of the same [[gender]]
#: ''he is their '''only''' son, infact, an '''only''' child''
# [[singularly]] superior; the best

====Related terms====
*[[only child]]

